I try to add indexer to custom runtime, derived from zerosharp. I thought that I have to copy code from SeeSharpSnake and it will start working.

So far, my `String` class has following implementation

```
public sealed class String {
        public readonly int Length;
        private char _firstChar;

        [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.IndexerName("Chars")]
        public unsafe char this[int index]
        {
            [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.Intrinsic]
            get
            {
                return Internal.Runtime.CompilerServices.Unsafe.Add(ref _firstChar, index);
            }
        }
    }
``` 

When I use string
```
var x = "hello"[3];
```
I have error
```
error CS0021: Cannot apply indexing with [] to an expression of type 'string'
```

Here my setup
class `String` located in the assembly `Runtime`. Usage of `String` class contains in separate project `App` and it fails there. 
If I start using indexer in the `Runtime` assembly, compiler does not complain.

